OL,5, A family of six have been living in a  
OL,6, one-bedroom flat because the social    
OL,7, housing they were assigned was         
OL,8, inaccessible to their disabled child.  
OL,10,FSeven-year-old Joel Verala uses a      
OL,11,Fwheelchair and is fed by a tube due to 
OL,12,Fquadriplegic cerebral palsy.           
OL,14,FThe house has three bedrooms but the   
OL,15,Ffamily have been told the adaptations  
OL,16,Fhe needs could take a year.            
OL,18,FCroydon Council said it had always     
OL,19,Finformed the family the work would take
OL,20,F"some months to complete".             
